---
description: Check Anchor IDL upgrades for account corruption before approving/committing
alwaysApply: true
---

Reordering, inserting, removing, or widening a field in an Anchor account struct silently
corrupts already-deployed accounts. It still compiles and tests still pass. Never approve
such a change by eye.

Before approving or committing an Anchor IDL change, run the checker — no install needed:

```bash
npx github:bhuvarloka/solana-upgrade-safety-skill <old-idl.json> <new-idl.json>
```

Old IDL from the last release (`git show <tag>:path/to/idl.json > /tmp/old.json`), new one from
the working tree. Act on the exit code:

- `0` — safe in place. Proceed.
- `1` — MIGRATE: corrupts deployed accounts. Stop. Add `--out ./out` to that command to generate
  the migration, or ship a new program ID.
- `2` — bad input, not a verdict. Fix paths; do not treat as corruption.
